---
import BaseHead from '../../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead
			title={`NYC Pastrami Ranking: ${SITE_TITLE}`}
			description="We pulled 30 ranked lists of NYC pastrami sandwiches from food blogs, newsletters, and local guides: then re-ranked every spot by its average position across the lists it appeared in."
		/>
		<style>
			.intro {
				margin-bottom: 2em;
				color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
				line-height: 1.7;
			}
			.methodology {
				background: rgba(var(--gray-light), 0.5);
				border-radius: 10px;
				padding: 1.25em 1.5em;
				margin-bottom: 2.5em;
				font-size: 0.9em;
				color: rgb(var(--gray));
				line-height: 1.65;
			}
			.methodology strong {
				color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
			}
			.ranking-list {
				display: flex;
				flex-direction: column;
				gap: 1.25em;
			}
			.entry {
				background: #fff;
				border-radius: 10px;
				padding: 1.25em 1.5em;
				box-shadow: 0 1px 4px rgba(var(--gray), 18%), 0 4px 16px rgba(var(--gray), 12%);
				display: grid;
				grid-template-columns: 3em 1fr auto;
				gap: 0 1.25em;
				align-items: start;
			}
			@media (max-width: 520px) {
				.entry {
					grid-template-columns: 2.5em 1fr;
				}
				.score-block {
					grid-column: 2;
					margin-top: 0.5em;
				}
			}
			.rank-num {
				font-size: 1.5em;
				font-weight: 800;
				color: rgb(var(--gray));
				line-height: 1.2;
				padding-top: 0.1em;
			}
			.rank-num.top3 {
				color: #b8860b;
			}
			.entry-body {
				min-width: 0;
			}
			.entry-name {
				font-size: 1.1em;
				font-weight: 700;
				color: rgb(var(--black));
				margin: 0 0 0.15em 0;
				line-height: 1.3;
			}
			.entry-location {
				font-size: 0.82em;
				color: rgb(var(--gray));
				margin-bottom: 0.5em;
			}
			.entry-note {
				font-size: 0.88em;
				color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
				line-height: 1.55;
			}
			.entry-note .tag {
				display: inline-block;
				font-size: 0.75em;
				font-weight: 700;
				letter-spacing: 0.07em;
				text-transform: uppercase;
				background: rgba(var(--gray-light), 0.8);
				color: rgb(var(--gray));
				border-radius: 4px;
				padding: 0.1em 0.5em;
				margin-right: 0.4em;
				vertical-align: middle;
			}
			.score-block {
				text-align: right;
				white-space: nowrap;
			}
			.avg-rank {
				font-size: 1.4em;
				font-weight: 800;
				color: rgb(var(--black));
				line-height: 1.1;
			}
			.avg-rank.top3 {
				color: #b8860b;
			}
			.avg-label {
				font-size: 0.68em;
				text-transform: uppercase;
				letter-spacing: 0.08em;
				color: rgb(var(--gray));
				display: block;
				margin-top: 0.2em;
			}
			.lists-count {
				font-size: 0.75em;
				color: rgb(var(--gray));
				margin-top: 0.5em;
			}
			.divider {
				border: none;
				border-top: 1px solid rgba(var(--gray), 15%);
				margin: 2em 0;
			}
.pickle-divider {
				display: flex;
				align-items: center;
				justify-content: center;
				gap: 1.25em;
				margin: 2em 0;
			}
			.pickle-divider::before,
			.pickle-divider::after {
				content: '';
				flex: 1;
				height: 1px;
				background: rgba(var(--gray), 20%);
			}
			.pickle-divider svg {
				width: 96px;
				height: auto;
				opacity: 0.82;
			}
			.sources-note {
				font-size: 0.82em;
				color: rgb(var(--gray));
				line-height: 1.6;
				margin-top: 2.5em;
			}
			.sources-note a {
				color: rgb(var(--gray));
			}
			/* Top 3: larger rank numeral, warm background, left border: structurally distinct from #22 */
			.entry.top3-entry {
				background: #fdf8ef;
				border-left: 4px solid #c4942e;
				padding-left: calc(1.5em - 4px);
				box-shadow: 0 2px 10px rgba(196,148,46,0.14), 0 6px 24px rgba(var(--gray), 10%);
				grid-template-columns: 3.5em 1fr auto;
			}
			.top3-entry .rank-num {
				font-size: 2.25em;
				line-height: 1.05;
				padding-top: 0.05em;
			}
			.top3-entry .entry-name {
				font-size: 1.2em;
			}
			.top3-entry .avg-rank {
				font-size: 1.75em;
			}
			.ticket-wrap {
				margin: 2.5em auto 0;
				max-width: 200px;
			}
			.ticket-wrap svg {
				width: 100%;
				height: auto;
				filter: drop-shadow(2px 3px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.15));
			}
		</style>
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<h1>NYC Pastrami, Ranked</h1>

			<p class="intro">
				There is no shortage of lists ranking pastrami sandwiches in New York City. The problem is that every list has its own agenda: a top pick on one is buried at the bottom of another. So instead of adding one more opinion, we pulled 30 ranked lists from food blogs, newsletters, and local guides published between 2024 and 2026, and let the aggregate do the talking.
			</p>
<div class="methodology">
				<strong>How this works:</strong> For each list, we recorded where every restaurant placed: 1st, 2nd, 3rd, and so on. We then calculated each restaurant's average rank across all the lists it appeared in. Lower average rank is better. A place that tops two lists beats a place that consistently sits at #5 on seven lists. No points for just showing up. Only mainstream publications were excluded (NYT, Eater, Grubstreet, Infatuation, Thrillist, and similar). 30 sources total; 23 restaurants ranked.
			</div>

			<div class="ranking-list">

				<div class="entry top3-entry">
					<div class="rank-num top3">1</div>
					<div class="entry-body">
						<div class="entry-name">Parkview Diner</div>
						<div class="entry-location">Bath Beach, Brooklyn</div>
						<div class="entry-note">
							<span class="tag">Tied #1</span>
							Won Best of Brooklyn pastrami in both 2024 and 2025. Almost entirely unknown outside the borough's local food circles, which is part of why the average rank looks so clean: the lists that mention it put it first.
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="score-block">
						<div class="avg-rank top3">1.0</div>
						<span class="avg-label">avg rank</span>
						<div class="lists-count">2 lists</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="entry top3-entry">
					<div class="rank-num top3">1</div>
					<div class="entry-body">
						<div class="entry-name">Moe's Pastrami &amp; Burger</div>
						<div class="entry-location">Prospect-Lefferts Gardens, Brooklyn</div>
						<div class="entry-note">
							<span class="tag">Tied #1</span>
							Opened 2023. Halal-certified. Won the Brooklyn Metropolis moving blog ranking outright and drew a 4/4 from the PeterKto food blog: edging Katz's 3/4 in a head-to-head. A commenter on Robert Sietsema's Substack called it the best in the boroughs after five decades of eating.
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="score-block">
						<div class="avg-rank top3">1.0</div>
						<span class="avg-label">avg rank</span>
						<div class="lists-count">2 lists</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="entry top3-entry">
					<div class="rank-num top3">3</div>
					<div class="entry-body">
						<div class="entry-name">Katz's Delicatessen</div>
						<div class="entry-location">Lower East Side, Manhattan</div>
						<div class="entry-note">
							Appeared on 14 lists, more than any other restaurant, and held the top position on most of them. The average rank of 1.3 confirms it is not just the most famous; it is genuinely the consensus best. The main complaints are the price ($28.95), the lines, and the tourist density. None of that changes what is in the sandwich.
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="score-block">
						<div class="avg-rank top3">1.3</div>
						<span class="avg-label">avg rank</span>
						<div class="lists-count">14 lists</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="entry">
					<div class="rank-num">4</div>
					<div class="entry-body">
						<div class="entry-name">House of Glatt</div>
						<div class="entry-location">Crown Heights, Brooklyn</div>
						<div class="entry-note">
							Glatt kosher butcher and deli that does not get much press outside of Crown Heights. Appeared on one qualifying list, where it placed second.
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="score-block">
						<div class="avg-rank">2.0</div>
						<span class="avg-label">avg rank</span>
						<div class="lists-count">1 list</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="entry">
					<div class="rank-num">5</div>
					<div class="entry-body">
						<div class="entry-name">Hometown Bar-B-Que</div>
						<div class="entry-location">Red Hook, Brooklyn</div>
						<div class="entry-note">
							<span class="tag">Fri-Sun only</span>
							Texas BBQ-style hot-smoked pastrami, available Friday through Sunday. John Tanner's BBQ blog argued it surpasses Katz's on raw flavor. For anyone who prefers the smoked brisket end of the spectrum over the steamed deli style, this is the pick.
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="score-block">
						<div class="avg-rank">2.8</div>
						<span class="avg-label">avg rank</span>
						<div class="lists-count">4 lists</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="entry">
					<div class="rank-num">6</div>
					<div class="entry-body">
						<div class="entry-name">2nd Avenue Deli</div>
						<div class="entry-location">Murray Hill / Upper East Side</div>
						<div class="entry-note">
							Consistently in the top three across seven separate lists. Hand-carved, thickly sliced, and made with brisket-cut pastrami. Critics frequently note the broth as a hidden strength. The UES location is more manageable than the Murray Hill branch on weekends.
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="score-block">
						<div class="avg-rank">3.1</div>
						<span class="avg-label">avg rank</span>
						<div class="lists-count">7 lists</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="entry">
					<div class="rank-num">7</div>
					<div class="entry-body">
						<div class="entry-name">Pastrami Queen</div>
						<div class="entry-location">UES / UWS / Moynihan Train Hall</div>
						<div class="entry-note">
							Anthony Bourdain's publicly stated favorite. Machine-sliced rather than hand-carved, which increases surface area and concentrates flavor. Appeared on 11 lists: second only to Katz's: and consistently landed in the top three. The Moynihan Hall location has made it more accessible than it used to be.
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="score-block">
						<div class="avg-rank">3.4</div>
						<span class="avg-label">avg rank</span>
						<div class="lists-count">11 lists</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="entry">
					<div class="rank-num">8</div>
					<div class="entry-body">
						<div class="entry-name">Junior's Restaurant &amp; Bakery</div>
						<div class="entry-location">Downtown Brooklyn</div>
						<div class="entry-note">
							<span class="tag">Tied #8</span>
							Better known for cheesecake, which may be why the pastrami tends to get overlooked. Appeared on four lists at an average position of 3.5.
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="score-block">
						<div class="avg-rank">3.5</div>
						<span class="avg-label">avg rank</span>
						<div class="lists-count">4 lists</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="entry">
					<div class="rank-num">8</div>
					<div class="entry-body">
						<div class="entry-name">Butcher Block</div>
						<div class="entry-location">Sunnyside, Queens</div>
						<div class="entry-note">
							<span class="tag">Tied #8</span>
							The only Queens entry in the top ten. Appeared on two lists at an average rank of 3.5. Largely unknown outside the neighborhood.
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="score-block">
						<div class="avg-rank">3.5</div>
						<span class="avg-label">avg rank</span>
						<div class="lists-count">2 lists</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="entry">
					<div class="rank-num">10</div>
					<div class="entry-body">
						<div class="entry-name">Liebman's Deli</div>
						<div class="entry-location">Riverdale, Bronx</div>
						<div class="entry-note">
							The only Bronx entry. Kosher, lean-cut pastrami with a 70-year history. Appeared on six lists and consistently described as the best-value option in the dataset. The trip to Riverdale keeps the tourist count low.
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="score-block">
						<div class="avg-rank">3.7</div>
						<span class="avg-label">avg rank</span>
						<div class="lists-count">6 lists</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="entry">
					<div class="rank-num">11</div>
					<div class="entry-body">
						<div class="entry-name">Sarge's Delicatessen</div>
						<div class="entry-location">Murray Hill, Manhattan</div>
						<div class="entry-note">
							Open 24 hours, which explains some of its following among people who did not plan ahead. Appeared on five lists at an average rank just under four. Reliable rather than exceptional.
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="score-block">
						<div class="avg-rank">3.8</div>
						<span class="avg-label">avg rank</span>
						<div class="lists-count">5 lists</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="pickle-divider" aria-hidden="true">
					<svg viewBox="0 0 120 48" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
						<!-- Pickle body -->
						<ellipse cx="60" cy="24" rx="54" ry="17" fill="#5a9a30" stroke="#2a5a10" stroke-width="2" transform="rotate(-6,60,24)"/>
						<!-- Light stripe -->
						<path d="M20,18 Q50,12 85,17 Q100,20 100,20" stroke="#8aca50" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" opacity="0.6"/>
						<!-- Bumps -->
						<circle cx="32" cy="22" r="3" fill="#4a8820" stroke="#2a5a10" stroke-width="1"/>
						<circle cx="60" cy="18" r="3" fill="#4a8820" stroke="#2a5a10" stroke-width="1"/>
						<circle cx="88" cy="22" r="3" fill="#4a8820" stroke="#2a5a10" stroke-width="1"/>
						<!-- End nub -->
						<ellipse cx="108" cy="23" rx="7" ry="5.5" fill="#4a8820" stroke="#2a5a10" stroke-width="1.5" transform="rotate(-6,108,23)"/>
					</svg>
				</div>

				<div class="entry">
					<div class="rank-num">12</div>
					<div class="entry-body">
						<div class="entry-name">USA Brooklyn Delicatessen</div>
						<div class="entry-location">Times Square, Manhattan</div>
						<div class="entry-note">Appeared on one list, placed fourth.</div>
					</div>
					<div class="score-block">
						<div class="avg-rank">4.0</div>
						<span class="avg-label">avg rank</span>
						<div class="lists-count">1 list</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="entry">
					<div class="rank-num">12</div>
					<div class="entry-body">
						<div class="entry-name">Mendy's NYC</div>
						<div class="entry-location">Midtown, Manhattan</div>
						<div class="entry-note">Appeared on one list, placed fourth.</div>
					</div>
					<div class="score-block">
						<div class="avg-rank">4.0</div>
						<span class="avg-label">avg rank</span>
						<div class="lists-count">1 list</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="entry">
					<div class="rank-num">12</div>
					<div class="entry-body">
						<div class="entry-name">Murray's Sturgeon Shop</div>
						<div class="entry-location">Upper West Side, Manhattan</div>
						<div class="entry-note">Known primarily as a smoked fish shop. Appeared on one pastrami list, placed fourth.</div>
					</div>
					<div class="score-block">
						<div class="avg-rank">4.0</div>
						<span class="avg-label">avg rank</span>
						<div class="lists-count">1 list</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="entry">
					<div class="rank-num">15</div>
					<div class="entry-body">
						<div class="entry-name">Mile End Delicatessen</div>
						<div class="entry-location">Boerum Hill, Brooklyn</div>
						<div class="entry-note">Montreal-style smoked meat rather than New York-style pastrami. A different sandwich, technically. Appeared on three lists at an average rank of 4.3.
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="score-block">
						<div class="avg-rank">4.3</div>
						<span class="avg-label">avg rank</span>
						<div class="lists-count">3 lists</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="entry">
					<div class="rank-num">16</div>
					<div class="entry-body">
						<div class="entry-name">S&amp;P Lunch (fmr. Eisenberg's)</div>
						<div class="entry-location">Flatiron, Manhattan</div>
						<div class="entry-note">Est. 1928, rebranded. Robert Sietsema called it third in the city and the best value in the dataset at $18. Appeared on three lists at an average rank of 4.7.
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="score-block">
						<div class="avg-rank">4.7</div>
						<span class="avg-label">avg rank</span>
						<div class="lists-count">3 lists</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="entry">
					<div class="rank-num">17</div>
					<div class="entry-body">
						<div class="entry-name">Majestic Delicatessen</div>
						<div class="entry-location">Times Square, Manhattan</div>
						<div class="entry-note">Appeared on one list, placed fifth.</div>
					</div>
					<div class="score-block">
						<div class="avg-rank">5.0</div>
						<span class="avg-label">avg rank</span>
						<div class="lists-count">1 list</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="entry">
					<div class="rank-num">18</div>
					<div class="entry-body">
						<div class="entry-name">Frankel's Delicatessen</div>
						<div class="entry-location">Greenpoint, Brooklyn</div>
						<div class="entry-note">
							Appeared on seven lists: the same count as 2nd Avenue Deli: but the average rank is 5.3 versus 3.1. Frequently praised for its pastrami Reuben specifically. The sandwich is well-regarded; it just tends to sit in the middle of the lists rather than at the top.
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="score-block">
						<div class="avg-rank">5.3</div>
						<span class="avg-label">avg rank</span>
						<div class="lists-count">7 lists</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="entry">
					<div class="rank-num">19</div>
					<div class="entry-body">
						<div class="entry-name">David's Brisket House</div>
						<div class="entry-location">Bed-Stuy / Bay Ridge, Brooklyn</div>
						<div class="entry-note">
							Halal-certified with 70 years of history in Brooklyn. Appeared on seven lists, the most of any restaurant outside Katz's and Pastrami Queen. The average rank of 5.9 reflects wide recognition but consistent lower placement: a presence rather than a destination.
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="score-block">
						<div class="avg-rank">5.9</div>
						<span class="avg-label">avg rank</span>
						<div class="lists-count">7 lists</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="entry">
					<div class="rank-num">20</div>
					<div class="entry-body">
						<div class="entry-name">Morgan's Brooklyn Barbecue</div>
						<div class="entry-location">Bed-Stuy, Brooklyn</div>
						<div class="entry-note">Appeared on one list, placed sixth.</div>
					</div>
					<div class="score-block">
						<div class="avg-rank">6.0</div>
						<span class="avg-label">avg rank</span>
						<div class="lists-count">1 list</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="entry">
					<div class="rank-num">20</div>
					<div class="entry-body">
						<div class="entry-name">Essen New York Deli</div>
						<div class="entry-location">Midwood, Brooklyn</div>
						<div class="entry-note">Appeared on one list, placed sixth.</div>
					</div>
					<div class="score-block">
						<div class="avg-rank">6.0</div>
						<span class="avg-label">avg rank</span>
						<div class="lists-count">1 list</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="entry">
					<div class="rank-num">22</div>
					<div class="entry-body">
						<div class="entry-name">Lenny's Grill and Deli</div>
						<div class="entry-location">Manhattan</div>
						<div class="entry-note">Appeared on one list, placed seventh.</div>
					</div>
					<div class="score-block">
						<div class="avg-rank">7.0</div>
						<span class="avg-label">avg rank</span>
						<div class="lists-count">1 list</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="entry">
					<div class="rank-num">22</div>
					<div class="entry-body">
						<div class="entry-name">Defonte Sandwich Shop</div>
						<div class="entry-location">Red Hook, Brooklyn</div>
						<div class="entry-note">Appeared on one list, placed seventh.</div>
					</div>
					<div class="score-block">
						<div class="avg-rank">7.0</div>
						<span class="avg-label">avg rank</span>
						<div class="lists-count">1 list</div>
					</div>
				</div>

			</div>

			<div class="ticket-wrap" aria-hidden="true">
				<svg viewBox="0 0 160 90" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" style="transform: rotate(2deg)">
					<!-- Ticket body -->
					<rect x="3" y="3" width="154" height="76" fill="#fdf6e3" stroke="#3a280a" stroke-width="1.5" rx="3"/>
					<!-- Header stripe -->
					<rect x="3" y="3" width="154" height="20" fill="#3a280a" rx="3"/>
					<rect x="3" y="18" width="154" height="5" fill="#3a280a"/>
					<!-- Header text -->
					<text x="80" y="16" text-anchor="middle" font-family="Georgia, serif" font-size="7.5" fill="#fdf6e3" letter-spacing="2.5">HOLD ONTO THIS TICKET</text>
